02:58.645 --> 03:00.897
Sam, what do you think of
Vivaldi at the ceremony?

03:00.897 --> 03:02.899
You can invite anybody
you want. I don't care.

03:02.899 --> 03:03.900
I'm not going to be...

03:03.900 --> 03:05.902
As a matter of fact,
nobody's going to be there

03:05.902 --> 03:07.770
'cause there's not
going to be a wedding,

03:07.770 --> 03:09.689
but if you want to
work here, that's fine.

03:09.689 --> 03:10.573
You got my blessings.

03:10.573 --> 03:13.409
I'm glad you've come around
to see the wisdom of it.

03:13.409 --> 03:14.694
Oh, there's wisdom in it.

03:14.694 --> 03:16.196
There's tons of wisdom.

03:16.196 --> 03:17.197
Let me tell you why.

03:17.197 --> 03:19.199
I want you to have
a front-row seat here

03:19.199 --> 03:20.667
for all the luscious babes

03:20.667 --> 03:23.169
I'm going to have marching
through here every night.

03:23.169 --> 03:24.671
As a matter of fact, from now on,

03:24.671 --> 03:28.041
it's casaba city, and
you're looking at the mayor.

03:28.041 --> 03:31.794
You'll pardon me if I don't
refer to you as "Your Honor."

03:31.794 --> 03:36.132
You know, I'm going down to the
Cape this weekend for a little R&R.

03:36.132 --> 03:38.134
That's Rhonda and room service.

03:38.134 --> 03:40.887
(all hooting)

03:40.887 --> 03:41.688
I love the Cape.

03:41.688 --> 03:44.190
We spent so many happy hours there.

03:44.190 --> 03:45.692
Sightseeing, talking...

03:45.692 --> 03:46.693
Yeah, well, Rhonda and I

03:46.693 --> 03:48.194
aren't going to have
any time for sightseeing.

03:48.194 --> 03:50.196
We're going to be just
coming up for air long enough

03:50.196 --> 03:51.564
to order some of that fish head soup.

03:51.564 --> 03:52.815
Bouillabaisse.

03:52.815 --> 03:54.817
No, I mean it.

03:56.819 --> 03:58.321
Fine.

03:58.321 --> 03:59.322
I couldn't care less.

03:59.322 --> 04:00.823
I'll just continue on,

04:00.823 --> 04:03.326
secure in the knowledge
that you love me.

04:03.326 --> 04:05.328
I did... I did not say I loved you.

04:05.328 --> 04:06.829
You proposed to me.

04:06.829 --> 04:08.331
Love and marriage go together.

04:08.331 --> 04:09.832
Why else would you propose to someone?

04:11.084 --> 04:13.419
Nevertheless do what you will,

04:13.419 --> 04:15.922
but keep in mind that
you might try to sabotage

04:15.922 --> 04:16.923
this tryst of yours

04:16.923 --> 04:19.926
because deep in your heart,
you know it's not right.

04:19.926 --> 04:21.310
We are.

04:21.310 --> 04:23.062
Oh, yeah, I see what you're doing here.

04:23.062 --> 04:25.064
You're trying to plant a
little seed in my brain.

04:25.064 --> 04:26.065
Oh, don't be silly.

04:26.065 --> 04:28.067
I know of nothing that
grows in solid rock.

04:28.067 --> 04:30.069
Yeah.

04:31.070 --> 04:32.939
Hi, everybody.

04:34.407 --> 04:36.909
(dejectedly): Hi, Diane. Welcome back.

04:36.909 --> 04:41.664
Carla, you don't seem
surprised that I'm working here.

04:41.664 --> 04:42.949
I knew you'd return.

04:43.449 --> 04:44.951
Your kind always does.

04:44.951 --> 04:47.954
Like roaches after atomic testing.

04:48.838 --> 04:50.673
Well, I must say I'm relieved

04:50.673 --> 04:52.175
to see you act this way.

04:52.175 --> 04:55.678
I was expecting something
a little more violent.

04:55.678 --> 04:56.679
No.

04:58.181 --> 04:59.599
I'm glad you're back.

04:59.599 --> 05:01.100
You see, I got this theory.

05:01.100 --> 05:04.103
If you and Sam hang around
each other long enough,

05:04.103 --> 05:06.472
one of you is going to kill the other.

05:06.472 --> 05:09.309
Now, if Sam kills you, fine.

05:09.309 --> 05:11.811
If you kill Sam, I'll turn you in,

05:11.811 --> 05:14.697
get a reward, and you'll get the chair.

05:14.697 --> 05:16.899
(imitates electrical crackling)

05:16.899 --> 05:19.068
Either way I come up a winner.

05:19.068 --> 05:20.903
I think we're becoming friends.

05:20.903 --> 05:22.905
Let's have a slumber party sometime.

05:23.906 --> 05:26.909
Hey, there's a kitty-cat in here.

05:26.909 --> 05:28.911
A guy gave 'em to me on
the way in this morning.

05:28.911 --> 05:32.915
You know my kids have been giving me a
lot of crap about not having any pets,

05:32.915 --> 05:35.418
so I figure Max here ought
to shut 'em up for a while.

05:35.418 --> 05:36.919
Well, what do you call

05:36.919 --> 05:37.920
the little one?

05:37.920 --> 05:38.921
What little one?

05:38.921 --> 05:41.424
You know, all that wheat's
making you hallucinate.

05:42.675 --> 05:45.011
Oh, great, she's having babies!

05:45.011 --> 05:46.512
There's another one!

05:46.512 --> 05:48.014
You're a farmboy.

05:48.014 --> 05:51.017
What are you supposed
to do to stop this?

05:52.518 --> 05:55.521
Well, it's too late
to go to the drugstore.

05:59.025 --> 06:03.529
I swear, I swear, this cat
was not pregnant when I got it.

06:04.030 --> 06:05.531
The minute it becomes a Tortelli,

06:05.531 --> 06:07.533
it starts dropping 'em like...

06:08.785 --> 06:09.619
(phone rings)

06:09.619 --> 06:11.120
Oh, yeah, there you are.

06:11.120 --> 06:13.005
Well, I'm off for my weekend, Diane.

06:13.005 --> 06:14.257
Cheers. Oh, by the way, did I tell you

06:14.757 --> 06:15.758
that Rhonda was double-jointed?

06:15.758 --> 06:17.427
Hey, Sam,

06:17.427 --> 06:18.761
it's for you.

06:22.265 --> 06:23.216
Yeah, hello.

06:23.216 --> 06:24.217
Oh, hey, Rhonda.

06:24.217 --> 06:26.719
I was just talking about you.

06:26.719 --> 06:30.723
Oh, oh, no, don't do this to me.

06:30.723 --> 06:32.225
Well...

06:32.725 --> 06:36.612
can't you be born again on Monday?

06:36.612 --> 06:39.148
All right, all right,

06:39.148 --> 06:40.450
Well, you, too.

06:40.450 --> 06:42.452
Whew, do you believe that?

06:42.952 --> 06:44.320
She canceled on me.

06:44.320 --> 06:45.655
Women.

06:45.655 --> 06:48.541
Reminds me of what my
Uncle Henry used to say.

06:48.541 --> 06:49.876
Oh, yeah? What was that, Woody?

06:49.876 --> 06:51.244
Women.

06:56.499 --> 06:59.001
Hey, uh, Sammy, don't let
Diane hear about Rhonda.

06:59.001 --> 07:01.754
She'll load that info into
her shotgun and take aim, huh?

07:01.754 --> 07:05.091
Yeah, no one is going to
ruin Sam Malone's weekend,

07:05.091 --> 07:07.093
no matter what Diane says.

07:07.093 --> 07:09.595
Yeah, hello, Vicki?

07:09.595 --> 07:12.598
Yeah, it's Sam Malone.

07:12.598 --> 07:16.602
Yeah, yeah, listen, uh,
how, how does the idea of,

07:16.602 --> 07:20.606
uh, 48 hours of sun and
surf up at the Cape grab ya?

07:20.606 --> 07:21.607
Oh, yeah?

07:21.607 --> 07:22.608
Well, if that grabs ya,

07:22.608 --> 07:24.610
how's the idea of me
grabbing you grab you?

07:24.610 --> 07:26.112
Yeah, all right.

07:26.112 --> 07:27.113
All right.

07:27.113 --> 07:28.114
Yeah, me, too.

07:28.114 --> 07:31.117
Okay, I, I'll see ya in
about two hours then, Vicki.

07:31.117 --> 07:32.618
All right. Bye-bye.

07:32.618 --> 07:33.619
CLIFF: Yeah.

07:33.619 --> 07:36.122
I thought her name was Rhonda.

07:36.122 --> 07:38.624
Well, uh... Rhonda canceled.

07:38.624 --> 07:39.876
But that's good.

07:39.876 --> 07:41.210
That's good because I like,

07:41.210 --> 07:43.095
I like Vicki better than Rhonda.

07:43.095 --> 07:46.098
As a matter of fact, I kind of
hope that, that Vicki cancels

07:46.098 --> 07:49.602
because I have somebody even
better waiting in the wings.

07:49.602 --> 07:50.853
I know. Me.

07:50.853 --> 07:52.054
No, no, not you.

08:00.780 --> 08:03.282
You know, Vicki, I just want you to know

08:03.282 --> 08:05.785
that this is going to
be the most beautiful,

08:05.785 --> 08:09.288
terrific, special
weekend of my entire life.

08:09.288 --> 08:12.158
Listen, you don't need to keep
selling me on this weekend.

08:12.158 --> 08:13.159
No, I...

08:13.159 --> 08:14.160
I'm sold. All right.

08:14.160 --> 08:15.161
I'm famished.

08:15.161 --> 08:16.412
I wish they'd take our order.

08:16.412 --> 08:17.246
Oh, they'll be here. Don't worry.

08:17.747 --> 08:19.499
Nothing's going to ruin
this weekend, I'll tell ya.

08:19.499 --> 08:22.301
Ah, perfect.

08:22.301 --> 08:23.803
Have you decided?

08:23.803 --> 08:24.720
What'll you have?

08:24.720 --> 08:26.222
Ah, what's the Catch of the Day?

08:26.222 --> 08:27.223
You mean besides me?

08:27.223 --> 08:28.724
(laughing)

08:28.724 --> 08:31.227
Ah, this is great. Isn't this great?

08:31.227 --> 08:32.727
We're having fun, right.

08:32.727 --> 08:33.729
I'll take the scallops.

08:33.729 --> 08:35.731
Yeah, uh, that... two of
those. That'll be good.

08:37.732 --> 08:38.734
Oh, geez!

08:38.734 --> 08:40.236
Are you sure you're okay?

08:40.236 --> 08:41.736
Yeah, are you kidding me?

08:41.736 --> 08:42.738
That was fun for me.

08:42.738 --> 08:44.240
Wasn't it fun for you?

08:44.240 --> 08:46.242
I mean, it's spontaneous, refreshing.

08:46.242 --> 08:47.243
Oh, it's great.

08:47.243 --> 08:48.244
I'll move you to another table.

08:48.244 --> 08:50.112
Don't you dare. This is perfect.

08:50.112 --> 08:52.748
Thank you very much.

08:52.748 --> 08:54.534
You know, someone tried to convince me

08:54.534 --> 08:56.919
that this weekend was going
to be a total disaster.

08:56.919 --> 08:58.621
VICKI: Really? Who?

08:58.621 --> 08:59.422
That person right there!

08:59.422 --> 09:01.924
Sam!

09:09.665 --> 09:12.969
What a surprise.

09:12.969 --> 09:14.337
Hello.

09:14.337 --> 09:15.588
Hello. I'm Vicki.

09:15.588 --> 09:16.589
I'm...

09:16.923 --> 09:18.391
Leaving immediately.

09:18.391 --> 09:19.225
Diane.

09:19.225 --> 09:21.227
Are you enjoying your weekend?

09:21.227 --> 09:23.729
Of course she's enjoying her weekend.

09:23.729 --> 09:25.231
It's a fantastic weekend.

09:25.231 --> 09:26.732
Did you notice your table's all wet?

09:26.732 --> 09:28.734
That's 'cause we want it that way.

09:28.734 --> 09:30.736
As a matter of fact, we ordered it wet.

09:30.736 --> 09:32.738
Hey, you know, I think it's drying out

09:32.738 --> 09:33.739
a little bit, don't you?

09:33.739 --> 09:35.241
Here you go. That's better.

09:35.241 --> 09:36.742
Excuse me, Miss.

09:36.742 --> 09:39.745
There's a telephone
call for you at the desk.

09:39.745 --> 09:41.113
Thank you.

09:41.113 --> 09:42.865
I'll be right back.

09:44.867 --> 09:48.371
I'll miss you.

09:48.371 --> 09:49.872
What the hell are you doing here?

09:49.872 --> 09:53.376
Mm, you know, all your talk
of a lovely weekend at the Cape

09:53.376 --> 09:55.878
made me realize how much I
needed to get away myself.

09:55.878 --> 09:57.380
It's just the most

09:57.380 --> 09:58.881
incredible coincidence

09:58.881 --> 10:00.883
that we ended up at the same place.

10:00.883 --> 10:01.884
I know what you're trying to do.

10:01.884 --> 10:03.886
You're trying to rattle
me, but the joke's on you,

10:03.886 --> 10:04.887
because I'm better under pressure.

10:04.887 --> 10:05.888
I don't rattle.

10:05.888 --> 10:07.890
Only when you shake your head.

10:09.775 --> 10:11.727
Have fun. Okay.

10:13.229 --> 10:14.230
You know, you just guaranteed

10:14.230 --> 10:16.732
this is going to be the
most perfect weekend ever.

10:19.235 --> 10:20.736
Oh, good, yeah, you're back.

10:20.736 --> 10:21.737
Yeah, that's perfect.

10:21.737 --> 10:23.739
Now why don't you sit down over there.

10:23.739 --> 10:25.741
This might be wet here.

10:25.741 --> 10:27.126
Sam? Hmm?

10:27.126 --> 10:28.744
I'm afraid I have to leave.

10:28.744 --> 10:31.914
Oh, God, no, don't say that, please.

10:31.914 --> 10:34.750
I'm sorry. Look, that was
my sister on the phone.

10:34.750 --> 10:35.751
Our grandmother's ill.

10:35.751 --> 10:37.253
I have to fly to Idaho.

10:37.253 --> 10:38.754
Why? You're not a doctor.

10:40.139 --> 10:41.090
Please, please, don't...

10:41.090 --> 10:42.475
Sam, I'm sorry this happened,

10:42.475 --> 10:43.759
but you're going to have

10:43.759 --> 10:45.728
to drive me back.

10:45.728 --> 10:47.229
No, no, uh...

10:47.229 --> 10:49.231
I have to stay here.

10:49.231 --> 10:50.733
Uh, I'll call you a cab.

10:50.733 --> 10:52.735
Well, as long as you
don't go out of your way.

10:52.735 --> 10:54.103
What, again, Vicki?

10:54.103 --> 10:56.605
Even rabbits take a break to eat.

11:00.993 --> 11:03.245
When you're finished there, go upstairs

11:03.245 --> 11:06.248
and help the lady in Mr.
Malone's room with her bags.

11:06.248 --> 11:07.750
WAITER: She's checking out?

11:07.750 --> 11:09.752
Her grandmother's ill.

11:09.752 --> 11:11.253
(Diane laughing)

11:14.623 --> 11:16.125
I'd heard she was dead.

11:16.125 --> 11:18.010
It's nice to know she's just sick.

11:24.633 --> 11:27.186
WOMAN (on TV): Pat,
I'd like to buy a vowel.

11:27.186 --> 11:28.637
A vowel?

11:28.637 --> 11:29.972
There are only two spaces left.

11:29.972 --> 11:31.023
She wants to buy a vowel.

11:31.023 --> 11:33.359
Where do they get these people?

11:33.359 --> 11:35.528
(knocking)

11:39.982 --> 11:40.983
Who is it?

11:40.983 --> 11:42.485
Room service.

11:43.486 --> 11:45.488
Oh, yeah. Yeah, good, thank you.

11:45.488 --> 11:46.989
Put... put it right over there.

11:46.989 --> 11:47.990
Okay.

11:55.498 --> 11:56.499
I bet you're wondering why

11:56.499 --> 11:58.000
I ordered two of everything

11:58.000 --> 11:59.502
when there's only me up here, huh?

11:59.502 --> 12:01.504
Uh, no, not really.

12:03.506 --> 12:06.008
Well, actually, it's 'cause
I want to give the impression

12:06.008 --> 12:07.393
that there are two people in the room.

12:07.393 --> 12:09.845
Well, you fooled me.

12:09.845 --> 12:11.230
Oh.

12:11.230 --> 12:13.015
Good, good, good.

12:14.517 --> 12:15.518
Where are my hot fudge sundaes?

12:15.518 --> 12:17.019
I couldn't fit 'em on the tray.

12:17.019 --> 12:18.020
I'll be right back up.

12:18.020 --> 12:19.522
All right. Great, great.

12:19.522 --> 12:21.524
Uh, make sure you parade around
the lobby a couple of times

12:21.524 --> 12:24.026
before you bring 'em on up. Will ya?

12:24.026 --> 12:25.528
Sure.

12:28.531 --> 12:30.032
(phone rings)

12:40.543 --> 12:41.427
Hello.

12:41.427 --> 12:42.294
Hi, Sam.

12:42.294 --> 12:43.679
How's it going up there?

12:43.679 --> 12:47.049
Uh, fine. Fine.

12:47.049 --> 12:48.050
(giggles)

12:48.050 --> 12:52.555
Oh, don't do that, Vicki. I'm ticklish.

12:52.555 --> 12:56.058
Sam, I feel an apology is in order.

12:56.058 --> 12:58.060
I may have made your friend Vicki

12:58.060 --> 12:59.812
a bit uncomfortable earlier today.

12:59.812 --> 13:01.647
Well, she's plenty
comfortable right now,

13:01.647 --> 13:03.649
so, uh, I'll pass on her message.

13:03.649 --> 13:04.533
Bye-bye, Diane.

13:04.533 --> 13:05.901
No, no, Sam.

13:05.901 --> 13:07.403
I wouldn't feel right

13:07.403 --> 13:09.905
unless I expressed my
feelings personally.

13:09.905 --> 13:11.907
Let me speak with her, please.

13:13.793 --> 13:16.295
Shoot.

13:17.296 --> 13:20.666
She's in the, uh, the
bathroom right now.

13:20.666 --> 13:23.752
She's tickling you from the bathroom?

13:23.752 --> 13:25.554
Well, she just went in there.

13:25.554 --> 13:29.425
She... she always runs into the
bathroom after she tickles me.

13:29.425 --> 13:31.594
Perhaps it's nausea.

13:33.929 --> 13:37.900
Sam, I, I really want to
apologize to her face-to-face.

13:37.900 --> 13:38.901
I'll be right up.

13:38.901 --> 13:40.352
No, no, no, no, don't...
(line disconnects)

14:17.890 --> 14:18.891
Oh, good, good, good.

14:18.891 --> 14:20.893
Do me a favor, will
ya? I'll pay you $50.

14:20.893 --> 14:22.394
I beg your pardon.

14:22.394 --> 14:23.395
Let's go, Harvey.

14:23.395 --> 14:25.397
No, no, no, please.
No funny stuff at all.

14:25.397 --> 14:27.900
Uh, come, come on now.
You'll be saving my life here.

14:27.900 --> 14:28.901
Come, come on in. Come in.

14:28.901 --> 14:29.902
Now hold it now. Just a minute here.

14:29.902 --> 14:31.403
I promise you.

14:31.403 --> 14:32.404
No weird stuff.

14:32.404 --> 14:34.406
I just want your wife
to go in the bathroom

14:34.406 --> 14:35.407
and make some noises.

14:35.407 --> 14:37.293
What kind of noises?

14:37.293 --> 14:39.128
